From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000006 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Maciej Pijanka <maciej.pijanka@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 5 Aug 2025 16:49:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 06/11] net: vlsi: add VSRVES01 ethernet MAC driver

Add the platform driver for the ethernet MAC integrated in the VLSI
VSRVES01 RISC-V SoC.  The driver covers:

  - rv_*/vs_* register map exposed via a void __iomem * / struct
    vsrves01_regmap union for ergonomic field access;
  - a memory-mapped MDIO bus driven by readl_poll_timeout();
  - threaded RX completion (devm_request_threaded_irq) draining two
    ping-pong RX memories at ETH_RXDATA;
  - a TX path with its own IRQ (devm_request_irq) and netif queue
    flow control;
  - PHY lifecycle through of_phy_get_and_connect() and the standard
    phy_start()/phy_stop() helpers;
  - ethtool drvinfo/link/msglevel ops;
  - a 512-byte raw register window exposed at sysfs "regmem" for
    bring-up debugging;
  - a force10mbps module_param used during FPGA bring-up.

The driver matches dt compatible "vlsi,vsrves01-mac" (binding added
earlier in this series) and depends on CONFIG_COMMON_CLK / selects
PHYLIB.

Known minor issues kept as-is for now (do not block bring-up):

  - sparse warns on field accesses such as &priv->regmap->cf because
    the regmap struct fields do not carry __iomem.  The union pattern
    is deliberate to keep the call sites compact; switching the entire
    file to ETH_<NAME>-offset addressing would touch every register
    access and is left for a follow-up.
  - The original out-of-tree driver had a spinlock-leak bug in
    vsrves01_mac_open() (two return -EAGAIN paths without
    spin_unlock_irq).  esmils port reworked the open path to register
    IRQs via devm_request_*irq() at probe time, so the bug no longer
    exists in this driver.

Origin: esmil/linux vsrv branch 29b289977925 (driver source only)

Co-developed-by: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Maciej Pijanka <maciej.pijanka@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Emil Renner Berthing <emil.renner.berthing@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Sungjoon Moon <sumoon@seoulsaram.org>
